Chatbot_LikeDislike: Having experimented with a mindfulness chatbot to deepen my meditation practices, I was met with some unexpected challenges. The chatbot felt impersonal, lacking the genuine understanding and empathy that human teachers or therapists might provide. There were times I felt frustrated by its technical limitations, offering generic or repetitive answers when I sought more nuanced guidance. Unlike a human guide, the chatbot couldn't provide real-time feedback during my meditation, leaving me to navigate challenges independently. I also began to question my growing dependency on the technology for such an intimate practice. Privacy became another concern; sharing my personal reflections and experiences with a bot made me uneasy about where my data might end up. The bot's tendency to oversimplify complex mindfulness concepts made me wonder if I was missing out on deeper insights. Overall, while it had its merits, I found the chatbot's approach lacked the flexibility and depth of human-led mindfulness sessions.

MindfulnessChanges_open: My belief was that mindfulness is limited to the action of acknowledging and processing thoughts and emotions. However, when those emotions harbour strong negativity, they can easily overcome an individual's true character and virtue. Thus, in order to be truly mindful, I now believe it is important to react to those constant thoughts and emotions logically while positively reinforcing the pros of the situation. It is important to maintain a balance between rational thinking skills and handling certain situations so that it protects one's wellbeing.
StressChanges_open: Through the practices that were completed, stress has definitely adopted a more positive definition in my perspective. Essentially, stress is a leading factor of poor performance and tendencies of anxiety, but if coped with in a healthy manner, it is a significant performance booster. If one perceives stress as a motivator instead of a competitor or weakness, it helps to reduce how overwhelming certain worrisome situations can be. It can act as a barrier between an individual and the feeling of defeated at the hand of responsibilities and worrisome events.
StudyExpectation_open: The training has made a noticeable effect on my life. I would ensure to complete the training after I had finished all my work for the day as that is when my well-being is most decreased. The training was an opportunity for me to self-reflect on the thoughts and emotions I experienced throughout the day but was unable to process and address them then. In fact, the training exceeded my expectations because I was actually able to apply the practices during certain moments in my personal life, from dealing with eating disorder urges, coping with high workload, and resolving family issues by perceiving situations through a more positive and logical lens.

StressChanges_open: my idea of stress did not change too much, I now understand dhow to better cope with stress and how to better understand where the stress is coming from.
StudyExpectation_open: the training exceeded my own expectations, i liked having the ability to talk to a bot that set my meditation goals based on what I told them. it was much easier than choosing what training I wanted to do based on a static list.
ChangesWithinSelf_open: nothing really changed about me during the study, i understand my own emotions a bit better and now can have more control of my mindset.
Suggestions_open: nope
Chatbot_LikeDislike: i really liked the chat bot and how it actually made comments and used what you wrote to pick out the best meditation method for you. it was better and more efficient than choosing how you want to meditate off a very vague list.

WB_changes_open: I learned how to better my focus, relationship with others and myself, and meditate
